article.headline: Princeton 60, Harvard 59
article.story: CAMBRIDGE, Mass. (AP) -- Noah Savage scored a jumper with two seconds left to lift Princeton to a 60-59 win over Harvard on Friday night. Harvard (12-8, 4-3 Ivy) led 59-53 after Matt Stehle scored two free throws with 1:17 remaining. Princeton's Edwin Buffmire converted two free throws and the Tigers' full-court press forced a turnover. Scott Greenman had a 3-pointer to make it 59-58 with 31 seconds left. On the next play, Buffmire deflected a pass and Princeton gained possession. The Tigers did not call time out and set up Savage for the winning field goal. After a 2-2 tie Princeton (6-12, 4-1) led the entire first half as Kyle Koncz had four 3-pointers. Harvard's Drew Housman sparked an 8-2 run as the Crimson closed to within 27-25 at halftime. Brian Cusworth's field goal tied it for Harvard on the first possession of the second half. Michael Beal sparked a 12-3 run which gave the Crimson a 51-43 lead with 5:11 left. Cusworth led Harvard with 20 points, and Koncz had 20 for Princeton.
